{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ba20654e-e921-4baf-a8ce-6cf4b375d9b9","content":"Here's the correct skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute | Example |\n|-----------|-----------|---------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` | `[Ignore(\"Bug #123 pending fix\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` | `[Fact(Skip = \"Bug #123 pending fix\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` | `[Ignore(\"Bug #123 pending fix\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` | `[Skip(\"Bug #123 pending fix\")]` |\n\n**Notes:**\n- For xUnit `[Theory]` tests, use `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` — same `Skip` property.\n- MSTest and NUnit both use `[Ignore]` but from different namespaces (`Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` vs `NUnit.Framework`).\n- All four frameworks support a reason string, which shows up in test runner output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"58fab59a-fa3f-4379-918c-b1816b0b980c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct skip/ignore attributes for each test framework. Let me invoke the relevant skill for this.","outputTokens":293,"requestId":"4C12:2F058A:DB30E3:1115503:6A012D4F"},"id":"1a4eb6da-52a6-4e8b-b05f-428be005cb3e","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:13:58.889Z","parentId":"416948a7-69e4-4d44-bb11-8e88c344fb0e"}
